>>42725149
>many different words there are for what's pretty much the same animal,
Keep in mind, you're having a conversation in English. We have adopted words from dozens of languages, including localized slang. When we don't discard an obsolete word, we often massage its meaning into a variation of something similar to add nuance to a conversation. Weasel indicating he Summer coat and stoat (or ermine) indicating a Winter coat is an excellent example. Other words indicate actual different species in different parts of the world, even if Americans apply an Asiatic term to a North American animal. And, excuse me if I fucked that up, since I didn't search wiki as I typed that, I'm going from memory because I don't think I've used the term ermine in 20 years or more.
